“Blood biomarker testing is like looking underneath the hood of a car. 
It makes me a much better competitive athlete. I can't imagine not using InsideTracker. It is vital to creating my health goals. InsideTracker helps me prioritize longevity. I want to be in coaching for a long time and I still want to be a great athlete 20 years down the line. I have really big goals that I want to accomplish. As I get older, I still want to be running and I still want to have plenty of energy for my athletes and my family.”

I’ve made some small manageable changes based on my results!
I’ve added in more soluble fiber like beans and oats to help my cholesterol. 
I’m also focusing more on my recovery and emphasizing sleep. I like to try and have a calm morning hour to myself to drink coffee, organize and stretch before my son wakes up!
Using my @insidetracker app daily has helped keep me accountable 👊🏼

node.text:
Today our @bowermantc athletes begin competition at the Tokyo Olympic Games!!

I’m taking a moment to feel extra grateful. 🙏🏼

A year ago we were grieving the loss of so much. Dreams derailed and postponed. Our world was upside down.

We are loving the steps along the way; soaking up the ability to travel and savoring connections with friends again.

In the last few weeks we went from the high altitude mountains of park City to sun kissed Hawaii and now to our final destination the Olympic Games in Tokyo!! 

Grateful and excited to be at my 5th Olympic Games is an understatement. ♥️🏟 #bowermantrackclub #bowermanbabes #bowermanbros

💗Missing my little family 💗

How lucky am I to go to my 5th Olympic Games……now as a coach! 

Also, how lucky am I to have such a supportive family that allows me to pursue my passions and goals!

But, dang it’s hard being away from my son and family. 

How lucky am I, to do what I love AND at the same time have so many people to miss.

Make Presto Pesto…..Like a BOSS!

Smear, slather, drizzle and dip this super easy pesto sauce on everything! 

This is a family favorite! I make huge batches all summer long for pastas dishes, dipping chips/veggies and smearing on toast or sandwiches!

With recent travel it’s been hard to keep up our morning routine. So it’s been lovely to fall back into our relaxed habits. Here is what our typical mornings at home look like.

5:00-6am Wake up (no alarm clock because my mommy clock can feel when baby Jack is about to wake)

6am-Drink coffee ☕️ and make Jack’s bottle

6-6:15am snuggle with Jack as he wakes up and drinks his bottle 

6:30-7am PLAY

7am-make breakfast for Jack. 
Our staple is @stonyfield yogurt cups. Jack likes them as is, but I’ve also been adding some fresh summer fruit or cereal for crunchy texture!

Jack has been growing like crazy….(check out his super long hair 🤣) and I’ve noticed his appetite increase as well! Grateful for companies like Stonyfield that value such high quality organic ingredients.

Ohhhhhh and did I say we are traveling again?! We are taking our first family flight today 😳 I appreciate any advice on entertaining a 14month old!🙏🏼✈️

node.text:
Tonight’s dinner!! 
Being on the road always makes me appreciate returning home to my kitchen where I can cook the foods that keep me at my best. I’ve been making this refreshing Greek Salad on repeat to hydrate and beat inflammation after summer run adventures. 

Did you know that foods like cucumbers hydrate our bodies better than water? This simple recipe is hidden in Run Fast. Cook Fast. Eat Slow. as the “Mediterranean Hummus Wrap” (RFCFES, p. 108), but I love it as a salad with grilled chicken or steak and Don’t Get Beet Hummus (RFCES, p. 73) with pita or tortilla chips for dipping.  

I crave salads like this all summer long and I always add handfuls of fresh herbs into the mix. Herbs like basil, cilantro, parsley, and mint not only make all of your summer meals taste better, they have a ton of antioxidant and anti-inflammatory benefits, making them amazing for recovery. After pounding the pavement or running around all day trying to keep up with Jack, I could use all the help I can get!

Here are some of my other favorite recipes full of fresh herbs (all are in Run Fast. Cook Fast. Eat Slow, my go-to cookbook for summer because the recipes are FAST):
- Thai Quinoa Salad (p. 90)
- Presto Pesto (p. 172)
- Pesto Pasta with Sardines (p. 148)
- Turkey Trot Meatballs (p. 147)  
- Immune-Boost Smoothie (p. 55)
- Green Goddess Tahini Dressing (p. 178) – soooo good on literally everything! #powerbowls

Photo by @natalie_cooks
